### Range Clause

The `range` clause iterates over elements of various data structures.

### Range Over Map

```go
m := map[string]int{"a": 1, "b": 2, "c": 3}

for key, value := range m {
    fmt.Printf("%s -> %d\n", key, value)
}

// Keys only
for key := range m {
    fmt.Println(key)
}
```

Map iteration order is intentionally randomized in Go.

### Range Over Channel

```go
ch := make(chan int)
go func() {
    for i := 0; i < 5; i++ {
        ch <- i
    }
    close(ch)
}()

for val := range ch {
    fmt.Println(val) // 0, 1, 2, 3, 4
}
```

The channel must be closed or the loop will deadlock.

### Range Over String

```go
s := "Hello, 世界"
for i, r := range s {
    fmt.Printf("byte index %d: %c (U+%04X)\n", i, r, r)
}
```

### Range Over Array/Slice Pointer

```go
arr := [3]int{10, 20, 30}
for i, v := range &arr {
    fmt.Println(i, v)
}
```

### Iteration Values

| Structure | Variables | Value Type |
|-----------|-----------|------------|
| array/slice | index, value | index: int, value: element |
| string | index, rune | index: int, rune: rune |
| map | key, value | same as K, V |
| channel | value | element type |
| pointer to array | index, value | same as array |

### Go 1.22+ Range Over Functions

Go 1.22 introduced experimental support for ranging over functions. Stable in Go 1.23:

```go
func Backward[E any](s []E) func(func(int, E) bool) {
    return func(yield func(int, E) bool) {
        for i := len(s) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {
            if !yield(i, s[i]) {
                return
            }
        }
    }
}

// Usage
for i, v := range Backward([]int{10, 20, 30}) {
    fmt.Println(i, v)
}
```

> **Key Point:** Range always copies the value. To modify elements in a slice, use the index to access `s[i]`.

codeExample:
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
    // Slice - modifying via range
    nums := []int{10, 20, 30}
    for i := range nums {
        nums[i] *= 2 // modify original
    }
    fmt.Println("doubled:", nums)

    // String - rune iteration
    for i, r := range "Go!" {
        fmt.Printf("byte[%d] = %c\n", i, r)
    }

    // Channel
    ch := make(chan int)
    go func() {
        for _, v := range []int{1, 2, 3} {
            ch <- v
        }
        close(ch)
    }()
    for v := range ch {
        fmt.Println("from chan:", v)
    }
}
